Here's how I'm doing it, in a new subclass of `interval`:

```
class MyInterval(interval):
    def complement(self) -> 'MyInterval':
        chain = itertools.chain(self, [[inf, None]])

        out = []
        prev = [None, neg_inf]
        for this in chain:
            if prev[1] != this[0]:
                out.append([prev[1], this[0]])
            prev = this

        return self.__class__(*out)
```

