@ayharano The issue here is that the schema view is not publicly available by default. I will update the default get_swagger_view() shortcut in a following release to default the schema to AllowAny, this way the spec is always accessible (though permissions will be enforced for the contents of the spec).

In the meantime, I suggest using a custom SwaggerView and setting permission_classes to `AllowAny`.

Example: 

```python
class SchemaView(views.APIView):
    exclude_from_schema = True
    renderer_classes = [
        OpenAPIRenderer,
        SwaggerUIRenderer,
    ]
    permission_classes = [permissions.AllowAny]

    def get(self, request, *args, **kwargs):
        generator = schemas.SchemaGenerator(title='My API')
        schema = generator.get_schema(request)

        return response.Response(schema)
```

