@jone i've investigated and you're right. the final reindex is indeed not streamed. we'll have to tackle this, i see two solutions:
- explicit `processQueue` call when all upgrades have been installed
- defer removing the log handler installed by `ResponseLogger` until after the transaction has been committed

@danfrankj Thanks for the contribution, Dan!

I'm of mixed minds about including this sort of feature. At this stage, apart from connection configuration, there is no "magic" state which can affect how code works in differing contexts. In fact, so far, the entire point of omniduct has been to abstract away details of the implementation so that every database duct operation works atomically. This feature seems to me to be something that could mess with that... where the order in which code cells run can change Duct state, and hence cause omniduct to run differently depending on code execution order.

I can see why this feature can be useful, I'm just not sure it's worth the sacrifice of atomicity. What do you think?

