@andreas-wolf, thanks for telling us about this problem.

The reason that I took out the documentation about the key from `cli.ini` was to *stop* people from trying to specify domains in `cli.ini`. Specifying domains there does not match our general understanding of how Certbot should be used or what these options mean, because it basically hard-codes a single set of domains system-wide, while we intend Certbot to be usable to manage many different certificates, each of which covers a completely different set of domains.

Removing the documentation about this key there has reduced the number of people who ran into bugs like this because fewer people think of the idea of specifying domains there. In parallel, #4479 says that this key should be completely ignored by the renewal script when it is placed in `cli.ini` (but apparently that didn't work in this case due to a further bug, which we'll need to try to fix).

